30/05/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Republika Srpska (RS) and Serbia say they will step up efforts and regularly exchange information regarding the possible whereabouts of war crimes fugitives, including Ratko Mladic and Radovan Karadzic.
RS Interior Minister Stanislav Cado met with Rasim Ljajic, the head of Serbia's national council for co-operation with UN war crimes tribunal, in Belgrade on Tuesday (May 29th).
They stressed that such co-operation is a priority for both the Serbian and RS governments.
In other news Tuesday, High Representative to Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) Christian Schwarz-Schilling froze funding of four main parties in the Federation of BiH -- HDZ BiH, HDZ 1990-HZ, SDA and SBiH.
The parties are being penalised for failing to agree on a new government in the canton eight months after the general elections.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 30/05/07;
Fena, RTRS, NTV Hayat - 29/05/07)
